text_for_analysis: Near Diggenahalli village in Bhadravati taluk, the Bhadra right bank, where about 300 cusecs of water has been flowing for the past 8 days, has broken its sluice gate. Due to this, farmers are facing water shortage for 25,000 acres of crops and their crops are drying up. I ask you to urgently repair the sluice gate. This is a small farmer who grows crops in the Bhadra canal... Madhu...

text_for_analysis: 4 Jana Sharanara Hijack Purana is a C. Shi. Background: Religious Guru: Sanganabasavanna (discoverer of Ishtalinga) Emblem: Ishtalinga Disciple: Sharana Revanasiddha Emblem: Ishtalinga Religion: Lingayat Basavanna's contemporary Sharana Revanasiddha was falsely claimed by the Panchacharyas to have arisen in the Someshwara plant in Kollipaki and made Sharana a myth under the name Renukacharya. First, he wrote the Purana of Chaturacharya, and then he added another Acharya and wrote the fictional Shikhamani Purana for the Panchacharyas, claiming that they had incarnated for ages. Chaturacharyas were originally devotees of Basava. Their names are as follows: 4 Basava devotees Chaturacharyas 1) Revanasiddha => Renukaradhya 2) Marulasiddha => Marularadhya 3) Ekorama => Ekoramaradhya 4) Panditaradhya => Panditaradhya + Vishwaradhya => Vishwaradhya Panchacharya Ah, the incarnation of Panchacharya by stealing the names of four Sharanas?! Brief Philosophy Shikhamani: Religious Guru: Kailasapati Shiva, Rudra, Shankara, Mahadeva Emblem: Janivar Disciple: Mythological Renukacharya Emblem: Sthavaralinga World Gurus: Panchacharya Emblem: Ishtalinga (invented by Basavanna) Religion: *Veerashaiva (previously for recognition 5 times) *Hindu Dharma (year ago) *Hindu Veerashaiva Lingayat (from the day before) *Sanatana Veerashaiva Dharma (from yesterday) What is Maya?! Is Maya dumbfounded? Basava Basava! Sharanappa Sajjan Anubhav Mantapa Goshti 11.03.2025 Mo: 9972724477

text_for_analysis: To the surrendered brothers, to the surrendered brothers, my heartfelt greetings on the occasion of the New Year, may God bless you all with good health, happiness, joy, and peace. On behalf of the entire Veerashaiva Lingayat community of Krishnarajapura assembly constituency, I pray to God. Brothers, let us preserve our cultural heritage, follow the path laid down by the Mathadhis and elders, protect the welfare of the community, extend a helping hand to the poor as much as we can. Let us preserve our unity, and when injustice happens, let us all face it together. Once again, I request you to extend your warmest greetings on the occasion of Ugadi. Greetings, Shivakumar, President
